cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper discusses the use of NDN architecture in a peer-to-peer file sharing application, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The use of peer-to-peer file sharing involves distributed computing, which falls under the scope of this category. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The BitTorrent protocol and the NDN architecture both involve data structures and algorithms for efficient file sharing, which falls under the scope of this category. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may discuss security aspects of the NDN architecture and how it affects the security of the file sharing application. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper may discuss the performance of the nTorrent application in terms of routing and forwarding using ndnSIM.
